rules: Rule1: If the court challenged the wine law, then the court upheld the wine law.

Rule16: Provided wine production is licensed, then under the condition that it is not the case that if the alcohol trade is not legal then fermentation is restricted, fermentation is prohibited.
Rule17: If Congress passed the wine bill, then wine production is approved.
Rule18: Either Congress passed the wine bill or Congress rejected the wine bill.

Rule22: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the producer violated rules then the producer is not fined, the producer's license is suspended.
Rule23: Provided that it is not the case that if the producer violated rules then the producer is not fined, the producer's license is not suspended.
Rule24: If it is not the case that if the president vetoed the wine law then the wine law was not amended, the court challenged the wine law.
Rule25: If it is not the case that if the alcohol trade is not legal then fermentation is restricted, then fermentation is not prohibited.
Rule26: If the alcohol trade is not legal, then fermentation is not banned.
